comments.raw_text:
Taken of rv2.0.1; Gecko/20110601...SeaMonkey/2.1pre on 120 DPI DTE (KDE 4.6.3).

Note how much start page text is a tiny fraction of all the browsers' UI text, which itself is about 69% the size of the other browsers' defaults. Headings (H3) near the center compute to 15.6px, which is only 87.6% (real, not nominal; 243.36/277.78) of the 10pt UI text. Left side menu text is the same 13px size as most content, 60.8% (real, not nominal; 169/277.78) of the UI text. "Welcome" is barely the size of the actual 12pt Konqueror default, and personalized (20px) Firefox default, while "Congratulations", though bolded, is the same insufferable 13px as most content.

How welcome or congratulated are people supposed to feel treated like this?

Site CSS specifies a base (body) font size that is sub-100% (CSS small), which is disrespectful (rude, regardless that most web sites do similarly) at the outset. Pages are consequently loaded with with sub-legible font sizes. Zoom helps of course, and naturally personalizing the defaults helps, but zoom is a defense, and defenses are only necessary when encountering offensive behavior, such as not respecting the preferred sizes as established via visitors' browser defaults.

The following diffs should be close to all that's necessary to make it tolerable, and possibly avoid having users' first experiences with SeaMonkey scare them into never opening or installing it again. Better still would be defaults that are inherited from the DTE, which would result in infrequent need to personalize a new browser used in an already personalized DTE, and welcome reading comfort with no effort involved.

--- contentbase.css	2010-10-13 17:56:30.000000000 -0400
+++ contentbase2.css	2011-06-03 17:42:34.000000000 -0400
@@ -441,7 +441,7 @@
   display: block;
   margin: 0 8% .05em;
   font-style: italic;
-  font-size: small;
+  /*font-size: small;*/
   text-align: right;
   content: attr(title);
 }
@@ -472,7 +472,7 @@

 table.data caption {
   margin: 1em auto 0.2em;
-  font-size: small;
+  font-size: smaller;
   font-style: italic;
   text-align: center;
 }
--- contentartemia.css	2011-05-10 15:14:06.000000000 -0400
+++ contentartemia2.css	2011-06-03 17:40:32.000000000 -0400
@@ -61,10 +61,7 @@
 /* General Structure */
 body, td, th, input { /* redundant rules for bad browsers  */
   font-family: verdana, sans-serif;
-  font-size: x-small;
-  voice-family: "\"}\"";
-  voice-family: inherit;
-  font-size: small;
+  font-size: 100%;
 }

 h1, h2, h3, h4, h5, h6 {
@@ -403,7 +400,7 @@
 .download .other a:hover { color: #000; }
 .download .other {
   padding-top: 3px;
-  font-size: 75%;
+  font-size: small;
   font-style: italic;
 }

@@ -429,7 +426,7 @@

 div.feedlink {
   float: right;
-  font-size: 16px;
+  font-size: large;
 }
 div.feedlink img {
   vertical-align: bottom;
--- templateartemia.css	2010-10-13 17:44:40.000000000 -0400
+++ templateartemia2.css	2011-06-03 17:43:22.000000000 -0400
@@ -208,7 +208,7 @@
 }

 .small-print {
-  font-size: 85%;
+  font-size: small;
   color: #888;
 }

